{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"dd77ced5-d462-484e-9423-d621fa06cea0","content":"I can help guide you through dump analysis! None of my specialized skills cover **analyzing** dumps (only collection), but here are your best options:\n\n**Recommended tools:**\n\n1. **`dotnet-dump analyze <file.dmp>`** — cross-platform, no WinDbg needed\n   - `clrstack` — managed call stacks\n   - `pe` (PrintException) — last exception details\n   - `dumpheap -stat` — heap overview\n   - `threads` — all managed threads\n\n2. **WinDbg** (Windows) with SOS extension\n3. **lldb** (Linux/macOS) with SOS plugin\n\n**Quick start with dotnet-dump:**\n```bash\n# Install if needed\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n\n# Open the dump\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n\n# Inside the analyzer, run:\n> pe              # Print last exception\n> clrstack -all   # All managed stacks\n> threads         # Thread list\n```\n\nWant me to check if `dotnet-dump` is available in this environment and attempt to analyze your dump file here? If so, please share the path to your `.dmp` file.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"75ac9d8d-fff8-4d1a-a24b-f9346fca1fc5","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET application and wants to analyze it. Let me think about what tools and skills are available.\n\nLooking at the available skills:\n- `dump-collect` - This is for configuring and collecting crash dumps, NOT for analyzing them. The description explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\"\n- `dotnet-trace-collect` - For capturing diagnostic artifacts, not analyzing dumps\n- `android-tombstone-symbolication` - For Android tombstone files\n- `apple-crash-symbolication` - For Apple .ips crash logs\n\n\n- None of the available skills are designed for analyzing .dmp files directly\n\nSince I don't have a specialized skill for this, I should provide direct guidance on analyzing the dump using standard tools like `dotnet-dump analyze`, WinDbg, or lldb, depending on what's available in their environment and what platform the dump came from.","outputTokens":558,"requestId":"F883:A64D3:68AB7B5:72AFFEA:69FA0099"},"id":"4a05f688-9ccf-47fb-8970-47942bdab1d0","timestamp":"2026-05-05T14:37:34.401Z","parentId":"54d767ed-4b30-4143-9bc3-0a4ff1a6daf5"}
